FAM Design was founded in 2020 by architect Frank Mataipule and interior designer Megan Freckelton. With more than 34 years of combined experience in architecture and interior design, our diverse portfolio includes both commercial and residential work with an emphasis on hospitality and residential design.  This experience allows us to offer our clients thoughtful and strategic design solutions.

Our approach at FAM is simple:  Work hard and have fun.

Services offered:

Interior Design and Architecture;
Interior space planning and programming;
Conceptual and schematic design;
Brand development;
Material specifications, detailing and documentation;
Furniture, fixture, art and accessory specifications, sourcing and procurement;
Construction and bid documents;
Consultant coordination;
Construction observation and documentation;
Architectural or interior design peer review.

The design process should be fun for all parties involved; does this mean we aren’t serious about all of this, not at all, we get down to business.

One of the largest architecture firms in Colorado brought Frank And Megan (FAM) together where they spent 13 years and 12 years respectively, leading and co-managing the design of various restaurant concepts, hotel and resort projects. In 2017, Frank and Megan accepted in-house co-Design Director roles with a rapidly expanding national restaurant group recognized by Fast Company as one of the most innovative companies in the world. There, they established and grew a design department to support its growth in the restaurant and hotel sector.

